The act or process of taking, apprehending, or seizing persons or property, by virtue of a writ, summons or other judicial order, and bringing the same into custody of the court for purpose of securing satisfaction of the judgment ultimately to be entered in the action. 

Source: [VA Circuit Court Civil Glossary](http://www.courts.state.va.us/courts/circuit/resources/manuals/cc_manual_civil/glossary.pdf)